-- Hitachi Shares Advance After First-Quarter Profit Beats Analyst Estimates
-- Jason Clenfield
-- 2010-08-02T00:07:41Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-08-02/hitachi-shares-advance-after-first-quarter-profit-beats-analyst-estimates.html

          
          
             Hitachi Ltd., Japan’s No. 3 company
by sales, rose in Tokyo trading after the company reported
first-quarter profit that exceeded analysts’ estimates.  
 Hitachi rose as much as 4 percent to at 366 yen at 9:06
a.m. on the Tokyo Stock Exchange, while the benchmark Nikkei 225
Stock Average climbed 0.5 percent.  
